  GROUP BY clause :- 
  =================

   => group by clause groups rows based on one or more columns to calculate
         min,max,sum,avg,count for each group , for ex to calculate dept wise
         total sal  first group the rows based on dept and apply sum function on each group
        
       EMP
       empno    ename   sal 	deptno
       100         A	  5000        10	
       101         B           3000	  20	   group by	10	8000
       102	     C	  4000	  30	=============?	20	9000
       103	     D	  6000 	  20			30	4000
       104         E           3000        10
  
       detailed  data 					summarized data				

 
 => GROUP BY clause converts detailed data into summarized data which is useful for analysis

syntax :-

   SELECT columns
   FROM tabname
   [WHERE cond]
   GROUP BY col1,col2,---
   [HAVING cond]
   [ORDER BY col ASC/DESC,---]

 Execution :-
 
  FROM
  WHERE
  GROUP BY
  HAVING
  SELECT
  ORDER BY 

 Ex :- 

 => display dept wise total salary ?

      SELECT deptno,SUM(sal)
      FROM emp
      GROUP BY deptno ;

